## 3️⃣ ARIA Attributes (When Needed)

ARIA attributes start with **`aria-`**

***

## 4️⃣ Commonly Used ARIA Attributes ✅

### ✅ `aria-label`

Provides an accessible name.



Used when text is missing or unclear.

***

### ✅ `aria-labelledby`

Refers to another element’s text.



✔ Better than `aria-label` when visible text exists

***

### ✅ `aria-describedby`

Adds extra description.



***

### ✅ `aria-hidden`

Hides content from screen readers.



⚠️ Still visible visually

***

### ✅ `aria-disabled`

For custom components (not native buttons).



***

### ✅ `aria-expanded`

Used for collapsible content.



***

### ✅ `aria-checked`

Used for custom checkboxes.



***

## 5️⃣ Roles (ARIA Roles)

Defines **what an element is** when not using semantic HTML.



Common roles:

*   `button`
*   `dialog`
*   `checkbox`
*   `alert`
*   `navigation`

