## 9️⃣ What NOT to Do ❌

❌ Overusing ARIA\
❌ Using ARIA instead of HTML\
❌ Adding roles to semantic elements\
❌ Ignoring keyboard navigation

***

## 🔑 Golden Rules of Accessibility ✅

1️⃣ Use **semantic HTML first**\
2️⃣ Add ARIA only when necessary\
3️⃣ Ensure keyboard navigation\
4️⃣ Always label form fields\
5️⃣ Test with screen readers

***

## ✅ Interview‑Ready Definition

> **Accessibility attributes make web content usable by people with disabilities by providing semantic meaning, labels, roles, and states to assistive technologies.**

